Use ASP.NET Core's `WebApplicationFactory<T>` from `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing`. It hosts your app in-memory with a test `HttpClient`—no real port needed.

**Setup:**

```csharp
// Install: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing

public class McpIntegrationTests : IClassFixture<WebApplicationFactory<Program>>
{
    private readonly HttpClient _client;

    public McpIntegrationTests(WebApplicationFactory<Program> factory)
    {
        _client = factory.CreateClient();
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task Initialize_ReturnsCapabilities()
    {
        var request = new
        {
            jsonrpc = "2.0",
            id = 1,
            method = "initialize",
            @params = new
            {
                protocolVersion = "2025-03-26",
                capabilities = new { },
                clientInfo = new { name = "test-client", version = "1.0" }
            }
        };

        var response = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", request);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();

        var body = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<JsonElement>();
        Assert.Equal("2025-03-26", body.GetProperty("result")
            .GetProperty("protocolVersion").GetString());
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task ToolsCall_ExecutesTool()
    {
        // Initialize first
        await InitializeSession();

        var request = new
        {
            jsonrpc = "2.0",
            id = 2,
            method = "tools/call",
            @params = new
            {
                name = "my-tool",
                arguments = new { input = "hello" }
            }
        };

        var response = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", request);
        var body = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<JsonElement>();

        Assert.False(body.GetProperty("result")
            .GetProperty("isError").GetBoolean());
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **No real port** — `WebApplicationFactory` uses an in-memory `TestServer`
- **Full pipeline** — middleware, DI, routing all execute as in production
- **Session handling** — if your server uses the `Mcp-Session-Id` header, capture it from the `initialize` response and attach it to subsequent requests
- **SSE streams** — use `HttpCompletionOption.ResponseHeadersRead` and read the stream line-by-line for SSE-based endpoints
- **Mock dependencies** — override services via `factory.WithWebHostBuilder(b => b.ConfigureServices(...))`

For stateful session tests, extract and forward the session header:

```csharp
var initResponse = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", initRequest);
var sessionId = initResponse.Headers.GetValues("Mcp-Session-Id").First();

_client.DefaultRequestHeaders.Add("Mcp-Session-Id", sessionId);
```
